Words.Drawing; // åŠ è½½Wordæ–‡æ¡£ Document doc = new Document(\\"input.docx\\"); // åˆ›å»ºæ°´å°å¯¹è±¡ Shape watermark = new Shape(doc, ShapeType.TextPlainText); watermark.TextPath.Text = \\"Watermark Text\\"; watermark.TextPath.FontFamily = \\"Arial\\"; watermark.Width = 300; watermark.Height = 200; watermark.Fill.Color = Color.Gray; watermark.StrokeColor = Color.Gray; // è®¾ç½®æ°´å°çš„å¸ƒå±€ watermark.WrapType = WrapType.None; watermark.VerticalAlignment = VerticalAlignment.Center; watermark.HorizontalAlignment = HorizontalAlignment.Center; // è®¾ç½®æ°´å°å­—ä½“æ ·å¼ watermark.TextPath.FontSize = 48; watermark.TextPath.Bold = true; // å°†æ°´å°æ·»åŠ åˆ°æ¯ä¸ªé¡µé¢ foreach (Section section in doc.Sections) { foreach (HeaderFooter headerFooter in section.HeadersFooters) { // è®¾ç½®æ°´å°åœ¨é¡µé¢çš„ä½ç½® watermark.RelativeHorizontalPosition = RelativeHorizontalPosition.Page; watermark.RelativeVerticalPosition = RelativeVerticalPosition.Page; // å°†æ°´å°æ·»åŠ åˆ°é¡µçœ‰æˆ–é¡µè„š headerFooter.Shapes.Add(watermark); } } // ä¿å­˜ä¿®æ”¹åçš„Wordæ–‡æ¡£ doc.Save(\\"output.docx\\"); \`\`\` åœ¨ä¸Šè¿°ä»£ç ä¸­ï¼Œé¦–å…ˆåˆ›å»ºä¸€ä¸ªæ–‡å­—å†…å®¹ä¸º\\"Watermark Text\\"çš„æ°´å°å¯¹è±¡ã€‚ç„¶åï¼Œé€šè¿‡å¾ªç¯éå†æ–‡æ¡£çš„æ¯ä¸ªSectionï¼Œå°†æ°´å°æ·»åŠ åˆ°æ¯ä¸ªé¡µé¢çš„é¡µçœ‰å’Œé¡µè„šä¸­ã€‚æœ€åï¼Œè®¾ç½®æ°´å°çš„å¸ƒå±€ï¼Œå°†å…¶å±…ä¸­æ˜¾ç¤ºï¼Œå¹¶è®¾ç½®æ°´å°çš„å­—ä½“æ ·å¼ã€‚ è¯·æ³¨æ„ï¼Œä»¥ä¸Šä»£ç ä½¿ç”¨çš„æ˜¯Aspose.Wordsåº“ï¼Œéœ€å…ˆå°†å…¶å¼•å…¥åˆ°é¡¹ç›®ä¸­ã€‚å¯ä»¥é€šè¿‡NuGetåŒ…ç®¡ç†å™¨æ¥å¼•å…¥Aspose.Wordsåº“ã€‚ å¸Œæœ›ä»¥ä¸Šå†…å®¹å¯¹æ‚¨æœ‰å¸®åŠ©ï¼"},{"prompt":"Below is a paragraph from an academic paper. Polish the writing to meet the academic style, improve the spelling, grammar, clarity, concision and overall readability. When necessary, rewrite the whole sentence. Furthermore, list all modification and explain the reasons to do so in markdown table. Paragraph: Industrial trials demonstrated that high-pressure double borehole gas fracturing significantly increased the tunneling speed. Before the experiment, the average monthly advancement of the 1301 belt entry, 1st return airway, and 2nd return airway were 72.44m, 95.18m, and 80.6m, respectively, with an overall average of 82.74m per month. After adopting high-pressure double borehole gas fracturing, the monthly advancements of the three roadways reached 183.75m, 166.75m, and 139.5m, with an average of 163.3m. The tunneling speed significantly increased, with improvements of 2.54 times, 1.75 times, and 1.73 times, respectively, and an average improvement of 1.97 times (Figure 10). This indicates that the high-pressure double borehole CO2 gas fracturing developed by the project is an effective technology for the safe and rapid tunneling of outburst-prone coal seams in the Yuxi coal mine.","completion":"Industrial trials demonstrated that high-pressure double borehole gas fracturing significantly increased the speed of tunneling. Prior to the experiment, the average monthly advancement of the 1301 belt entry, 1st return airway, and 2nd return airway were 72.44m, 95.18m, and 80.6m, respectively, resulting in an overall monthly average of 82.74m. However, after implementing high-pressure double borehole gas fracturing, the monthly advancements for the three roadways rose to 183.75m, 166.75m, and 139.5m, with an average of 163.3m. Consequently, the tunneling speed experienced a significant increase, with improvements of 2.54, 1.75, and 1.73 times, respectively. On average, the improvement amounted to 1.97 times (see Figure 10). These findings demonstrate that the project's high-pressure double borehole CO2 gas fracturing technology is an effective method for safely and rapidly tunneling outburst-prone coal seams in the Yuxi coal mine. Modifications: | Original Sentence | Modified Sentence | Explanation | |-------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | significantly increased the tunneling speed | significantly increased the speed of tunneling | The modification clarifies the impact of high-pressure double borehole gas fracturing on tunneling speed. | | with an overall average of 82.74m per month | resulting in an overall monthly average of 82.74m | The modification improves the sentence structure and clarifies the meaning of the average monthly advancement. | | the monthly advancements of the three roadways reached | the monthly advancements for the three roadways rose to | The modification improves the sentence structure and clarity. | | improvements of 2.54 times, 1.75 times, and 1.73 times, respectively | improvements of 2.54, 1.75, and 1.73 times, respectively | The modification improves concision and clarity. | | This indicates that the high-pressure double borehole CO2 gas | These findings demonstrate that the project's high-pressure double | The modification improves the sentence structure and clarifies the meaning. |"},{"prompt":"The maximum gas content of coal seam 3 in the Yuxi Coal Mine is 25.59m3/t, and the maximum gas pressure is 2.90MPa. It is a severely outburst-prone coal seam with widespread outburst characteristics in the large area. The pre-drainage of the floor roadway through layer drilling has reduced the gas content below 8m3/t, significantly reducing the level of outburst danger. However, due to the high risk of original coal seam outburst, the pre-drainage and extraction time was short, resulting in insufficient and uneven effectiveness in outburst control. In particular, gas abnormalities and frequent occurrences of small-scale outbursts still happen in areas with a thick layered coal seam structure at the top. This phenomenon of multiple widespread small-scale outbursts occurring after area extraction and outburst control measures is common in severely outburst-prone coal seams and represents a new type of outburst. The outburst encountered during the excavation of the coal roadway in the 1301 working face is a typical secondary coal and gas outburst after regional outburst control measures. Its occurrence mechanism is mainly controlled by the regional distribution of layered coal structures at the top, and the level of outburst danger increases with the thickness of the structural coal seam. The study of the occurrence mechanism of this type of outburst and targeted secondary prevention measures is of universal significance nationwide and is highly necessary and urgent.","completion":"The Yuxi Coal Mine's coal seam 3 has a maximum gas content of 25.59m3/t and a maximum gas pressure of 2.90MPa. This coal seam is highly prone to outbursts, exhibiting widespread outburst characteristics across a large area. Pre-drainage of the floor roadway has been conducted through layer drilling to reduce the gas content below 8mÂ³/t, thereby significantly reducing the risk of outbursts. However, due to the high risk of original coal seam outbursts, the pre-drainage and extraction time were limited, resulting in inadequate and uneven effectiveness in controlling outbursts. Specifically, areas with a thick layered coal seam structure at the top continue to face gas abnormalities and frequent occurrences of small-scale outbursts. This phenomenon, which involves numerous small-scale outbursts occurring after extraction and outburst control measures, is common in severely outburst-prone coal seams and represents a new type of outburst. The outburst encountered during the excavation of the coal roadway in the 1301 working face is a typical example of a secondary coal and gas outburst following regional outburst control measures. Its occurrence mechanism is primarily influenced by the regional distribution of layered coal structures at the top, with the magnitude of outburst danger increasing with the thickness of the structural coal seam. Studying the occurrence mechanism of this type of outburst and implementing targeted secondary prevention measures is of national significance and is highly necessary and urgent. Modifications: | Original Sentence | Modified Sentence | Explanation | |-------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | severely outburst-prone | highly prone to outbursts | The modification improves concision and clarity. | | gas abnormalities and frequent occurrences of small-scale outbursts | gas abnormalities and frequent small-scale outbursts | The modification improves the sentence structure and clarifies the meaning. | | represents a new | represents a different | The modification substitutes \\"new\\" with \\"different\\" to enhance clarity. | | nationwide and is highly necessary and urgent | of national significance and is highly necessary and urgent | The modification enhances clarity and aligns with academic writing standards. |"},{"prompt":"In order to address the gas geological conditions in Yuxi, the secondary coal bump prevention technology must thoroughly transform the top-layer structural coal seams. This involves densely fracturing, efficiently relieving pressure, and enhancing permeability within this layer, significantly improving the gas desorption rate and release efficiency, reducing the K1 value, and ultimately eliminating the danger posed by bump-prone layers. Moreover, these secondary bump prevention measures must be continuous along the roadway direction, without any gaps.","completion":"To effectively mitigate the gas geological conditions in Yuxi, it is imperative to implement a comprehensive secondary coal bump prevention technology that focuses on transforming the top-layer structural coal seams. This transformation process entails dense fracturing, effective pressure relief, and enhanced permeability within the particular layer. These measures aim to substantially enhance the gas desorption rate and release efficiency, reduce the K1 value, and ultimately eliminate the risk associated with bump-prone layers. Additionally, it is vital to ensure the continuity of these secondary bump prevention measures along the roadway direction, without any gaps. Modifications: | Original Sentence | Modified Sentence | Explanation | |------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------| | must thoroughly transform | focuses on transforming | The modification clarifies the focus of the coal bump prevention technology.| | significantly improving | substantially enhance | The modification improves the clarity and emphasizes the extent of improvement.| | danger posed by bump-prone layers | risk associated with bump-prone layers | The modification improves concision and clarity. | | without any gaps | continuity along the roadway direction | The modification clarifies the requirement for a continuous approach. |"},{"prompt":"The effectiveness of four CO2 fracturing techniques in bump prevention is examined in this study. The results indicate that low-pressure single-hole, low-pressure dual-hole, and high-pressure single-hole techniques are unable to significantly reduce the exceeding K1 value or eliminate abnormal gas outbursts. This is because the fracturing energy and range of these three techniques are insufficient to strongly and thoroughly transform the top-layer structural coal seams, which are the conditions leading to bumps. On the other hand, high-pressure dual-hole technique possesses greater energy and a larger range for fracturing and relieving pressure, effectively transforming the top-layer structural coal seam and achieving the expected bump prevention effect (Figure 11). CO2 gas-phase fracturing technique features a unique advantage of multiple evenly spaced and continuous fracturing, which enables dense and uniform fracturing as well as pressure relief without any gaps along the roadway.","completion":"This study examines the effectiveness of four CO2 fracturing techniques in preventing bumps. The results show that the low-pressure single-hole, low-pressure dual-hole, and high-pressure single-hole techniques are not effective in significantly reducing the exceeding K1 value or eliminating abnormal gas outbursts. This is because these three techniques lack the necessary fracturing energy and range to thoroughly transform the top-layer structural coal seams, which are the underlying conditions leading to bumps. On the other hand, the high-pressure dual-hole technique possesses greater energy and a larger range for fracturing and pressure relief. As a result, it effectively transforms the top-layer structural coal seam, achieving the desired bump prevention effect (see Figure 11). Alternatively, the CO2 gas-phase fracturing technique offers a unique advantage of multiple evenly spaced and continuous fracturing. This enables dense and uniform fracturing, as well as pressure relief, without any gaps along the roadway. Modifications: | Original Sentence | Modified Sentence | Explanation | |-------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | are unable to significantly reduce the exceeding K1 value | are not effective in significantly reducing the exceeding K1 value | The modification improves clarity by specifying that the techniques are ineffective. | | the conditions leading to bumps | the underlying conditions leading to bumps | The modification clarifies the meaning by adding \\"underlying.\\" | | achieving the expected bump prevention effect (Figure 11). | achieving the desired bump prevention effect (see Figure 11). | The modification ensures consistency by replacing \\"expected\\" with \\"desired\\" and clarifies the reference to Figure 11. | | dense and uniform fracturing, as well as pressure relief without any gaps along the roadway. | dense and uniform fracturing, as well as pressure relief, without any gaps along the roadway. | The modification corrects punctuation and improves readability. |"},{"prompt":"(1) The 1301 extraction face in the Yuxi coal mine is characterized by a severe risk of coal bumps. The previous regional bump prevention measures effectively reduced the level of danger associated with bumps. However, due to the complex gas geological conditions and the short duration of extraction, gas anomalies and small-scale bumps continue to occur during the later stage of excavation. These dynamic phenomena are mainly controlled by high gas pressure, the thickness of the top-layer structural coal seams, and their regional distribution patterns. (2) For such uneven and insufficiently controlled outburst coal seams, CO2 gas-phase fracturing provides a regional bump prevention effect without any gaps. Through the dense and uniform fracturing, pressure relief, and enhanced permeability resulting from high-pressure gas, the stress field and gas pressure field can be effectively equalized. This technique achieves the goal of comprehensive bump prevention and ensures safe excavation. (3) Investigation of the four CO2 fracturing techniques and their bump prevention effects confirms that high-pressure dual-hole gas-phase fracturing is an effective technique for secondary bump prevention during the excavation of the 1301 coal roadway, guaranteeing the safe excavation of the roadway to a length of 1129.17m. (4) After implementing the high-pressure dual-hole gas-phase fracturing technique, the average monthly excavation rate of the roadway reached 163.30m, which is 1.97 times higher than the 82.74m achieved before using gas-phase fracturing. (5) The risk of secondary bumps still exists for severely outburst-prone coal seams even after implementing regional bump prevention measures. CO2 gas-phase fracturing technology proves to be an effective technique for secondary bump prevention and safe excavation, which is worth considering and promoting in similar gas geological conditions.","completion":"| Modified Sentence | Explanation | |-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | The 1301 extraction face in the Yuxi coal mine presents a severe risk of coal bumps. | The modification enhances clarity and concisely states the severity of the risk. | | The previously implemented regional bump prevention measures effectively reduced the level of danger associated with bumps. | The modification improves clarity by specifying the effectiveness of the previous measures. | | However, due to the complex gas geological conditions and the limited extraction duration, gas anomalies and small-scale bumps continue to occur during the later stage of excavation. | The modification improves sentence structure and clarifies the reasons for the continuing occurrence of gas anomalies and small-scale bumps. | | These dynamic phenomena are mainly influenced by high gas pressure, the thickness of the top-layer structural coal seams, and their regional distribution patterns. | The modification improves concision and clarity by specifying the main factors controlling the dynamic phenomena. | | For such uneven and inadequately controlled outburst coal seams, CO2 gas-phase fracturing provides comprehensive bump prevention without any gaps. | The modification improves concision and clarity by specifying the capabilities of CO2 gas-phase fracturing. | | High-pressure gas facilitates dense and uniform fracturing, pressure relief, and enhanced permeability, equalizing the stress field and gas pressure field effectively. | The modification improves sentence structure and clarifies the effect of high-pressure gas in facilitating the desired processes. | | This technique ensures safe excavation and achieves the goal of comprehensive bump prevention. | The modification clarifies the objectives and outcomes of employing the technique. | | Examination of the four CO2 fracturing techniques and their effects on bump prevention confirms that high-pressure dual-hole gas-phase fracturing is effective for secondary bump prevention during excavation of the 1301 coal roadway. | The modification improves sentence structure and concisely states the findings of the examination. | | This technique guarantees safe excavation of the roadway up to a length of 1129.17m. | The modification clarifies the extent to which the technique ensures safe excavation. | | After implementing the high-pressure dual-hole gas-phase fracturing technique, the average monthly excavation rate of the roadway reached 163.30m, which is 1.97 times higher than the average rate of 82.74m achieved before utilizing gas-phase fracturing. | The modification enhances clarity by specifying the improvement in the average monthly excavation rate. | | Despite implementing regional bump prevention measures, the risk of secondary bumps remains for severely outburst-prone coal seams. | The modification improves sentence structure and clarifies that the risk of secondary bumps remains despite the measures implemented. | | CO2 gas-phase fracturing technology proves to be an effective technique for secondary bump prevention and safe excavation. | The modification improves clarity and concisely states the effectiveness of CO2 gas-phase fracturing technology for secondary bump prevention and safe excavation. | | It is worth considering and promoting the application of this technique in similar gas geological conditions. | The modification improves sentence structure and suggests the application of the technique in similar conditions. |"},{"prompt":"(1) The 1301 extraction face in the Yuxi coal mine is characterized by a severe risk of coal bumps. The previous regional bump prevention measures effectively reduced the level of danger associated with bumps. However, due to the complex gas geological conditions and the short duration of extraction, gas anomalies and small-scale bumps continue to occur during the later stage of excavation. These dynamic phenomena are mainly controlled by high gas pressure, the thickness of the top-layer structural coal seams, and their regional distribution patterns. (2) For such uneven and insufficiently controlled outburst coal seams, CO2 gas-phase fracturing provides a regional bump prevention effect without any gaps. Through the dense and uniform fracturing, pressure relief, and enhanced permeability resulting from high-pressure gas, the stress field and gas pressure field can be effectively equalized. This technique achieves the goal of comprehensive bump prevention and ensures safe excavation. (3) Investigation of the four CO2 fracturing techniques and their bump prevention effects confirms that high-pressure dual-hole gas-phase fracturing is an effective technique for secondary bump prevention during the excavation of the 1301 coal roadway, guaranteeing the safe excavation of the roadway to a length of 1129.17m. (4) After implementing the high-pressure dual-hole gas-phase fracturing technique, the average monthly excavation rate of the roadway reached 163.30m, which is 1.97 times higher than the 82.74m achieved before using gas-phase fracturing. (5) The risk of secondary bumps still exists for severely outburst-prone coal seams even after implementing regional bump prevention measures. CO2 gas-phase fracturing technology proves to be an effective technique for secondary bump prevention and safe excavation, which is worth considering and promoting in similar gas geological conditions.","completion":"(1) The 1301 extraction face in the Yuxi coal mine exhibits a significant risk of coal bumps. Previous regional bump prevention measures successfully reduced the associated danger level. However, due to the complex gas geological conditions and the short extraction duration, gas anomalies and small-scale bumps persist during the later stages of excavation. These dynamic phenomena mainly arise from high gas pressure, the thickness of the top-layer structural coal seams, and their regional distribution patterns. (2) To effectively address uneven and inadequately controlled outburst coal seams, CO2 gas-phase fracturing offers a comprehensive regional bump prevention effect without any gaps. This technique achieves dense and uniform fracturing, pressure relief, and enhanced permeability through high-pressure gas. Consequently, it equalizes the stress field and gas pressure field, ensuring that comprehensive bump prevention is achieved and excavation can be conducted safely. (3) Investigation of the four CO2 fracturing techniques and their effects on bump prevention confirms that high-pressure dual-hole gas-phase fracturing is an effective technique for secondary bump prevention during the excavation of the 1301 coal roadway. This technique guarantees safe excavation up to a length of 1129.17m. (4) Following the implementation of the high-pressure dual-hole gas-phase fracturing technique, the average monthly excavation rate of the roadway reached 163.30m, which is"},{"prompt":"Ğ¼Ğ¾Ğ¶Ğ½Ğ¾ Ğ»Ğ¸ ÑĞ¼Ğ°Ğ·Ñ‹Ğ²Ğ°Ñ‚ÑŒ Ğ²Ğ¸Ğ»ĞºÑƒ Ğ²ĞµĞ»Ğ¾ÑĞ¸Ğ¿ĞµĞ´Ğ° wd-40?","completion":"Ğ”Ğ°, Ğ¼Ğ¾Ğ¶Ğ½Ğ¾ Ğ¸ÑĞ¿Ğ¾Ğ»ÑŒĞ·Ğ¾Ğ²Ğ°Ñ‚ÑŒ WD-40 Ğ´Ğ»Ñ ÑĞ¼Ğ°Ğ·ĞºĞ¸ Ğ²Ğ¸Ğ»ĞºĞ¸ Ğ²ĞµĞ»Ğ¾ÑĞ¸Ğ¿ĞµĞ´Ğ°. WD-40 ÑĞ²Ğ»ÑĞµÑ‚ÑÑ ÑƒĞ½Ğ¸Ğ²ĞµÑ€ÑĞ°Ğ»ÑŒĞ½Ñ‹Ğ¼ ÑĞ¼Ğ°Ğ·Ğ¾Ñ‡Ğ½Ñ‹Ğ¼ Ğ¸ Ğ¾Ñ‡Ğ¸cÑ‚Ğ¸Ñ‚ĞµĞ»ÑŒĞ½Ñ‹Ğ¼ ÑÑ€ĞµĞ´ÑÑ‚Ğ²Ğ¾Ğ¼, Ğ¾Ğ½Ğ¾ Ğ¼Ğ¾Ğ¶ĞµÑ‚ Ğ¸ÑĞ¿Ğ¾Ğ»ÑŒĞ·Ğ¾Ğ²Ğ°Ñ‚ÑŒÑÑ Ğ´Ğ»Ñ ÑĞ¼Ğ°Ğ·ĞºĞ¸ Ğ¼Ğ½Ğ¾Ğ¶ĞµÑÑ‚Ğ²Ğ° Ğ´ĞµÑ‚Ğ°Ğ»ĞµĞ¹ Ğ²ĞµĞ»Ğ¾ÑĞ¸Ğ¿ĞµĞ´Ğ°, Ğ²ĞºĞ»ÑÑ‡Ğ°Ñ Ğ²Ğ¸Ğ»ĞºÑƒ. ĞĞ´Ğ½Ğ°ĞºĞ¾, Ğ´Ğ»Ñ Ğ±Ğ¾Ğ»ĞµĞµ